# Analysis of the Main Target Image

## Count & Layers
The structure consists of 7 blocks arranged in 3 layers:
- Bottom layer: 2 blue cube blocks 
- Middle layer: 1 yellow rectangular block
- Top layer: 1 red house-shaped block with an arch and 3 orange triangular roof pieces

## Spatial Relationships
- Bottom layer: Two blue cubes (identical in size) positioned side by side with a gap between them
- Middle layer: A horizontal yellow rectangular block placed across the two blue cubes, bridging them
- Top layer: A red house-shaped block with an arched doorway sits on top of the yellow rectangle, and 3 orange triangular pieces form a roof on top of the red block

# Required Blocks from the Dictionary

Based on the target structure, I need the following blocks:
- 2 blue cubes (index 7)
- 1 yellow rectangular block (index 10)
- 1 red arched block (index 1)
- 3 orange triangular roof pieces (indices 13, 14, and 16)

# Assembly Order

```
{
   Step1: Move block with index 7
   Step2: Move block with index 7
   Step3: Move block with index 10
   Step4: Move block with index 1
   Step5: Move block with index 13
   Step6: Move block with index 14
   Step7: Move block with index 16
}
```
